Roundtable Updates (each group member to contribute) 	

•	Daria Dziura: Suggested that the platform needs an Admin role for moderation (deleting accounts/listings) and a Member role for swapping. She also suggested that the User should be a parent class for both
•	Katarzyna Lacek: Suggested that our Code of Conduct needs to be updated. She proposed that members should have an option to suggest changes for the platform and that we need a clear hierarchy for items (Books, Records, etc.).
•	Emmanuel Boateng: Suggested that members should be able to message each other, rate users after a swap, and report any inappropriate content. He also noted that Admins must be able to reset member passwords if they forget them.

Discussion points 	

•	Code of Conduct: We agreed to revise this to make sure the platform stays friendly and safe for swapping.
•	Inheritance: We liked the parent/child class idea for the database because it makes the roles of Admin and Member very clear.
•	Safety: We spent time talking about the reporting feature. We want members to be able to flag bad listings or "mean" comments immediately.
•	Community Building: We decided that the rating system is the best way to build trust so people know who is a "good" swapper.

